                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Page 1: The book of the hours (Saatat), containing various prayers with numerous admixtions in Agau -- Page 96: The canticles of the Prophets. The same as in manuscript no.3, but without the last three canticles from the New Testament -- Page 104: Psalm 118 -- Page 128: A Hymn on the passage of the Red Sea -- Page 131: The prayer of Moses (Exodus 15) followed by Psalms and fragments of Psalms -- Page 150: The book of Ezra. Identical with text published by Joseph Halevy in his Teezaza Sanbat, Paris 1902, pages 57-79, but with many variant readings. The same book is listed under the heading Apocalypse of Ezra in Wrights catalogue of Ethiopic manuscripts in the British Museum under XXVI, 7. -- Page 174: Other prescriptions of the Sabbath -- Page 175: Various prayers -- Page 226: The death of Moses (Mota Muse)
                        </summary>

